flowPara.flowSpan: In nature, animals must often decide between exploiting a resource site or leave it to explore potentially better ones.
5-HT is a neuromodulator that has been implicated in a variety of functions involving persistence in exploiting a site for uncertain reward1.

flowRoot.flowPara: The Flipping Task | By licking, mice exploits either one of two spouts.

flowPara.flowSpan: At any given moment, only one spout delivers reward and can deplete stochastically. In turn the other spout becomes active. Mice must infer the state of the spout they are exploiting (fresh or depleted) and run on the treadmill to switch between them2,3.
